</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It seems to me there are more pressing needs in our society for the anti-fur 
people to pursue than passing out leaflets at theater openings and black-tie 
galas ("Drive Is Mounted to Make Furs Extinct," Nov. 20). 
</P>
<P>
Do they also protest leather jackets, shoes, handbags and belts? How many of 
them abstain from eating meat? Why don't they also pass out cards in 
restaurants that read, "Eating meat promotes the idea that it is acceptable to 
kill an animal to appease the appetite. Please don't eat meat." It would appear 
this zealous group is so intent upon foisting their beliefs upon others that 
they even slip their cards into fur wearers' pockets . . . "discreetly," of 
course. 
