<P>
** 1/2 Mary-Chapin Carpenter, "Shooting Straight in the Dark," Columbia. 
Carpenter's third album harks back a bit to the lengthy, finely detailed 
character studies of her debut while retaining the greater pop accessibility 
that made her second such a leap forward, commercially and artistically. 
</P>
<P>
Too often she limits herself to straight reportage in her missives from the 
battlefields of love and life; you wish she'd delve more into analysis and 
commentary. But at least you always get the sense there's a lively, probing 
mind at work. Carpenter is interviewed on Page 67. RANDY LEWIS 
