<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WAY TO ACHIEVE REAL DEPRESSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Sean Mitchell's Nov. 25 article, "Misery" director Rob Reiner says, "You 
can't know real depression until you've had great wealth." 
</P>
<P>
Did he try that line on the parking valet mentioned in the story, who might be 
relieved to know he's never been really depressed? 
</P>
<P>
May I suggest that Reiner get in his Mercedes or Porsche, drive down to 
South-Central Los Angeles, find a woman whose 6-year-old child has just been 
killed in a drive-by shooting and tell her how she's not experiencing "real, 
abject depression" because she isn't rich yet. He might just learn what the 
title of his new movie really means. 
</P>
<P>
DOUGLAS McEWAN, Hemet 
</P>
</TEXT>
