<HEADLINE>
<P>
KING OF THE MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Daniel Cerone's Nov. 18 article about film adaptations of Stephen King's 
writings: Why is it when a great novel is made into a mediocre movie the author 
is ultimately blamed? 
</P>
<P>
If you loved "Christine" or "It" you cannot assume that the screen versions 
will be equivalent experiences. It is the filmmakers' responsibility to produce 
a meritorious adaptation. 
</P>
<P>
DANA THOMPSON 
</P>
<P>
Tujunga 
</P>
