<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
FOOD; 
</P>
<P>
WHAT'S SMOKIN'? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
IF YOU LOVE the outdoorsy flavor of meats and fish smoked slowly over hickory 
or mesquite but aren't crazy about getting out the smoker for small quantities 
of food, consider the Stovetop Smoker Cooker. It allows you to prepare just 
enough for one meal -- in very little time and without the bother of constantly 
running outdoors. 
</P>
<P>
It consists of a heavy stainless-steel pan that looks like a cake pan, a drip 
tray, a cooking rack and a lid. You simply place the chips in the pan, then add 
the chicken breasts, fish, even vegetables atop the food rack, and cover. Any 
fat drips into the tray below, and the food steams healthfully in its own 
juices, while the wood chips impart a smoky flavor. 
</P>
<P>
 C.M. International's Stovetop Smoker Cooker is available at Mrs. Gooch's and 
Gelson's markets.ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Stovetop Smoker 
</P>
