COLLEGE NEWS: SCHOOL OF MUSIC GETS $760,000 IN DONATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Azusa Pacific University has received two substantial gifts that will bolster 
financial aid and assist the music school at the interdenominational Christian 
school. 
</P>
<P>
The estate of John Newhouse of Arcadia has donated $333,357 to underwrite 
student scholarships. Nancy Loncaric of Long Beach has given $175,000 to the 
School of Music. Total contributions announced at the school's annual 
fund-raising dinner totaled $760,000. 
</P>
<P>
Additional good news for the Azusa school is that enrollment is up 7.7%, to 
3,159 students, over this time last year. This increase comes at a time when 
other area schools are having to adjust to enrollment declines, said Ron 
D'Avis, media-relations coordinator. 
