</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six San Marino High School students leave for Germany later this month after 
winning the Los Angeles Times' Ambassadors to Europe competition, co-sponsored 
by Lufthansa Airlines. 
</P>
<P>
The students' team was one of the five top scorers among the 600 Southern 
California teams that entered the competition, which tested high school 
students' knowledge of European economy, culture, geography, news and current 
events. 
</P>
<P>
From Dec. 9 to 15, all five teams, accompanied by their teachers, will lunch 
with German students in their homes, visit the state parliament in Wiesbaden 
and tour the University of Heidelberg. 
