<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
<P>
* Allow fuchsias to rest from now until February when you would prune them 
back. 
</P>
<P>
* Don't rush on lifting dahlias. Foliage should be allowed to ripen off and 
turn yellow, or the bulbs will be robbed of energy for next year's growth. 
</P>
<P>
* Sweet alyssum can be sown from seed over bulb beds; they'll bloom with the 
bulbs next spring. 
</P>
<P>
* Cool-season perennial vegetables can be planted now -- artichokes, asparagus 
and rhubarb. 
</P>
</TEXT>
