FINNS AGREE TO EXTRADITE AEROFLOT HIJACK SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HELSINKI, Finland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Finland said Friday it would extradite to the Soviet Union a Russian who 
hijacked an Aeroflot jet to Helsinki in October. 
</P>
<P>
Neutral Finland has already returned two other Soviet hijackers to the Soviet 
Union this year. 
</P>
