<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The holiday season is upon us once again, and once again you will have the 
opportunity to watch "It's a Wonderful Life" or "Miracle on 34th Street" almost 
every other day. To break the holiday rut, watch a different kind of Christmas 
story. The Original Theatre Works of Cerritos College will present the Lee Korf 
award-winning comedy "Your Father Owned a Reindeer" on selected dates beginning 
Friday through Dec. 15 in the Burnight Studio Theatre. 
</P>
<P>
New York playwright Richard Holland has written an offbeat story revolving 
around the holiday celebration of the eccentric Scavulo family. The assorted 
cast of characters includes Rebecca Bailey as Carol Scavulo, the oldest Scavulo 
daughter; Charles Gorman as Izzy, Carol's anthropologist husband; Dorothy 
McClane as Martha, matriarch of the Scavulo clan; Fred Lanciloti as Sal, the 
Scavulo patriarch; Susan Alderette as Sharon Scavulo and Jeff Tucker as Brian, 
her lover, a musician and waiter; Cliff Schneider as Doug Scavulo, the 
perpetual salesman; and Alecs Vildosola as Donnie Scavulo, a fashion designer. 
</P>
<P>
The play is set in Izzy and Carol's living room, adorned with various 
archeological and anthropological artifacts that are decorated by Carol with 
traditional Christmas trimmings. Martha lobbies for her first grandchild by 
giving Carol a sexy negligee as a present. Sal celebrates Christmas in his own 
special way, by betting on a horse named Christmas Tree. But personal quirks 
and hard-fought attempts at communication do not dampen the family's 
expectations of a happy holiday. 
</P>
<P>
More than 200 plays were submitted nationally for the Lee Korf Playwriting 
Award, and this one by Holland was one of three winners. Holland became a 
professional playwright in 1981. He has served as assistant director for "The 
Chosen," Chaim Potok's $3.5-million off-Broadway musical, co-founded 
Stagewrights, a nonprofit playwrights' theater, and has had finalist entries in 
the O'Neill Competition and the Rosenthal New Play Prize. Holland is currently 
working on a musical adaptation of Mark Twain's "The Prince and the Pauper," 
which is expected to play Broadway in the fall of 1992. 
</P>
<P>
"Your Father Owned a Reindeer" will be presented at 8 p.m. Friday, Saturday, 
Dec. 13, 14 and 15 and at 2:30 p.m. Dec. 9. Burnight Studio Theatre is on the 
Cerritos College campus, 11110 Alondra Blvd., Norwalk. Tickets are $7.50 and 
can be purchased at the door. This play contains some adult language and may 
not be suitable for children. For more information, call 924-2100. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Cast members in Cerritos College comedy, front from left, Susan 
Alderette, Fred Lanciloti, Jeff Tucker, Dorothy McClane, Alecs Vildosola; top, 
Cliff Schneider, Rebecca Bailey, Charles Gorman. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
