<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEAVE THEM OUT OF IT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Ex-Navy Trainer Attacks U.S. Use of Sea Animals" (Nov. 13): 
</P>
<P>
I find David Reames' position that he is "concerned about human beings" quite 
ironic. 
</P>
<P>
Reames argues that the use of marine mammals endangers the lives of human 
soldiers because of the animals' unreliability and, therefore, the mammals 
should not be used in military combat. 
</P>
<P>
Yet, what about the endangered lives of the marine mammals? 
</P>
<P>
The sea animals are trained to please the trainer and are unaware of the 
potentially destructive task they are performing, and could easily make a 
mistake and not realize the seriousness of their actions. As one protester's 
placard stated, "How can dolphins know friends from foe?" 
</P>
<P>
Man should fight his own battles and leave the innocent creatures out of it! 
</P>
<P>
CYNTHIA M. KELLNER, La Jolla 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
