<HEADLINE>
<P>
AILING WARD LEADS TITANS PAST BUTLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Agee Ward, bruised thigh and all, gave Cal State Fullerton a shot in the arm 
Saturday night, scoring 25 points and grabbing 12 rebounds to lead the Titans 
to a 79-76 victory over Butler before 1,201 in Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Ward, a 6-foot-5 junior who started the Titans' season opener against Lamar, 
has come off the bench the last two games since being injured. 
</P>
<P>
Ward gave Fullerton 23 strong minutes, converting four offensive rebounds into 
baskets and scoring 16 of his points in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Center Aaron Wilhite added 12 points and forward Ron Caldwell had 10 to 
complement an inside game that carried the Titans on a night their outside game 
went cold. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton guard Joe Small made his first shot early in the game but finished 
three for 16, including one of six from three-point range. 
</P>
<P>
"No player is going to have a good game every night -- that's why it's a team 
game," Titan Coach John Sneed said. "Someone else has to step in, like Agee." 
</P>
<P>
It seemed as if no Titan was a threat in the final six minutes, when Fullerton 
blew an 11-point lead. The Bulldogs scored 11 consecutive points, nine by 
forward Darin Archbold, to make the score 72-72 with 2:45 left. Archbold 
finished with 31 points. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton caved in against Butler's full-court press, turning the ball over 
three times during Butler's run. Wilhite finally broke the spell with two free 
throws at the 2:10 mark, and Small made a jumper and two free throws to keep 
Fullerton ahead in the final 1:28. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce Bowen blocked Jermaine Guice's three-pointer as the game ended to secure 
the victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
