<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLAYER ARRESTED AFTER FAN IS HIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CONWAY, Ark. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marlo Johnson of Mesa College, the NAIA's leading rusher, was charged with 
battery for hitting a fan with his helmet after his team's victory in a playoff 
game Saturday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson had rushed for 47 yards in 18 carries to help Mesa to a 10-9 victory 
over Central Arkansas. Billy Leach, director of the Department of Public Safety 
at Central Arkansas, said witnesses saw the tailback run from the sideline to a 
nearby track and hit a Central Arkansas fan in the face with his helmet. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Jim Lawson, was taken to a hospital and treated for a broken jaw, 
authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
