<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-NHL COACH HAS HEART ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTREAL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michel Bergeron, former coach of the Quebec Nordiques and New York Rangers, was 
in stable condition Saturday after suffering a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
Bergeron, 44, was taken to a hospital near his home in Rosemere, Quebec, after 
complaining of intense chest pains Friday night. He had been watching the 
Montreal-Washington game on television. 
</P>
</TEXT>
