<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE HIGH SCHOOL VOLLEYBALL FINALS; 
</P>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR WINS DIVISION I TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corona del Mar High won its second State Division I girls' volleyball title 
Saturday night with a 15-3, 15-5, 11-15, 15-8 victory over Mountain View St. 
Francis in the championship game at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar (28-1) won its 26th consecutive match. 
</P>
<P>
The school's last state title was in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
Lara Carlsen had 14 kills, Tracy Schriber had 13 and Stacy Petersen added 12 
for Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
In Division II, La Habra won its second consecutive state title with a 15-5, 
15-1, 15-5 victory over King City. The Highlanders (26-0) won their 45th 
consecutive match in a two-year span. 
</P>
<P>
Missy Clements had 14 kills and Zrinka Kristich added 12 kills and seven aces 
for the Highlanders. 
</P>
<P>
Amy McMahon had eight kills to lead King City (23-3). 
</P>
<P>
In Division III, Linden, playing in the finals for the third consecutive year, 
won its first title with a 15-7, 3-15, 4-15, 15-5, 15-3 victory over 
Bakersfield Garces. 
</P>
<P>
Cammie Stewart had 12 kills and Erika Probat added eight to lead Linden (24-2). 
Garces finished 17-9. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
