<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 HELD IN TEEN-AGER'S SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Inglewood teen-ager who was shot in the stomach and head during an argument 
Thursday evening died Friday at Harbor-UCLA Medical Center, Hawthorne police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Martin Guadalupe Enriquez, 18, was a passenger in a car when he became involved 
in an argument with two youths in another car at Imperial Highway and Truro 
Avenue about 8 p.m., Hawthorne Police Detective Mike Lee said. 
</P>
<P>
As the argument escalated, Lee said, Enriquez got out of the car. He was shot 
twice before his assailants drove away. No one else was injured, Lee said. 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne police later arrested David Perez, 18, of Hawthorne, and Abel Gaeta, 
18, of Inglewood. The two youths were being held at the Hawthorne jail, Lee 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Neither the victim nor the two suspects are known gang members, Lee said. The 
shooting "started as a verbal confrontation," Lee said, and "doesn't appear to 
be gang-related at this time." 
</P>
</TEXT>
