<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FLORES SEEKS TO CLOSE SCRAP YARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Councilwoman Joan Milke Flores has asked city zoning officials to 
consider declaring a San Pedro scrap yard a nuisance and eventually move for 
its closure, unless steps are taken to reduce noise, traffic and debris. 
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Zoning Administrator Bob Janovici, Flores said the action 
against Hiuka America Corp. follows four years of complaints about its 
operations from community residents and business leaders. The 20-acre yard, 
which opened in 1986, is at 2100 N. Gaffey St., just off the Harbor Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
Flores' action follows months of talks with company officials, who have argued 
that Hiuka has done all it can to reduce noise, traffic and other effects, 
while searching for a more suitable location. 
</P>
</TEXT>
