<HEADLINE>
<P>
DILLON HELPS VALHALLA GETS PAST SOUTHWEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Valhalla boys' basketball team trailed by five at halftime but a 
high-scoring third quarter helped boost the Norsemen to a 68-64 victory over 
Southwest at the Norsemen/Warhawk Tournament at Valhalla Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla (2-0) outscored Southwest 23-6 in the third quarter to lead 51-39 
going into the final quarter of the game. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Dillon led the Norsemen with 22 points and teammate Mike Nalu scored 17. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Hilltop Tournament 
</P>
<P>
Sweetwater 68, Mira Mesa 45 -- Melvin Rushing scored 24 points and had 10 
rebounds for Sweetwater. Mendel Nafaneck and Patereos Woodson each scored 16 
points for Sweetwater. Guillermo Arcadia led Sweetwater with 12 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Kearny 85, Chula Vista 50 -- Jerome Green scored 19 points for Chula Vista. 
Kearny led, 52-28, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Hilltop 53, Point Loma 38 -- Courtney Brown scored 20 points for Hilltop. Point 
Loma was led by Eddie Greer with 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
Bonita Vista 68, La Jolla 33 -- Bonita Vista took a 31-9 halftime lead. Rope 
Perry scored 14 points for La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Redwood Classic 
</P>
<P>
Marian Catholic 66, Mendocino 60 -- Marian trailed by 17 at the end of the 
third quarter but outscored Mendocino, 26-9, in the fourth quarter to send the 
game into overtime. Marian (3-1) then outscored Mendocino, 6-0, in overtime. 
Joe Lagula led Marian with 29 points and 13 rebounds. JaMarr Brown added 25. 
</P>
