<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE FINDS A TEAM IT CAN HANDLE, 109-90 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THERESA MUNOZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following three lopsided road losses, Cal State Northridge gained its first 
victory in its inaugural Division I basketball season, 109-90, over Northern 
Arizona Saturday night at Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Seven Matadors scored in double figures, led by Todd Bowser with 17 points and 
David Keeter with 16. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge ran off 15 consecutive points to open the game, including a steal 
and dunk by Keith Gibbs, a steal and layup by Andre Chevalier, two three-point 
baskets by Kyle Kerlegan and a three-pointer by Keeter. 
</P>
<P>
The Lumberjacks (0-3) couldn't handle the Matadors' full-court zone press, 
which forced seven turnovers in the first six minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Northern Arizona ended the drought on a basket by Steve Williams, but 
Northridge pushed the lead to 20-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120290-0225 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 316781 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 2, 1990, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
