<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
AGOURA'S DROSSIN PREVAILS IN KINNEY WEST REGIONAL IN RECORD-TYING TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM PERERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deena Drossin of Agoura High tied the six-year-old Woodward Park course record 
in winning the Kinney West regional cross-country title Saturday in Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
The Charger senior clocked 17 minutes 7.8 seconds over the 5,000-meter 
(3.1-mile) circuit, equaling the mark set by Marnie Mason of Klamath Falls High 
(Ore.) in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
The top eight finishers in the boys' and girls' races qualified for the 
national championships, to be held in San Diego on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Two of Drossin's Marmonte League rivals finished among the top eight. 
</P>
<P>
Jeannie Rothman of Westlake timed 17:16 in finishing second and Channel 
Islands' junior Veronica Barajas was eighth in 17:47. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon senior Dave Hartman placed third in 15:04 behind winner Louie Quintana 
(14:49) of Arroyo Grande and James Menon (15:01) of San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 59, Northeastern 58 -- Julie Arlotto scored on a layup 
with four seconds left after an inbounds pass from Bridgette Ealy at half court 
to give CSUN the consolation championship of the Fresno State tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Ealy, who did not play in the first half because of a strained calf muscle, 
scored 12 points on six-of-seven shooting and had three rebounds and two 
assists in 18 minutes. Arlotto finished with eight points and had six assists. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge (2-3), which had fallen behind by five before mounting its 
second-half comeback, shot a sizzling 62% from the field. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks tournament: Sophomore midfielder Ian Leiviska scored five goals 
in 3-1 and 2-1 wins over Santa Paula and Bosco Tech in the first round of pool 
play for Burbank (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 1, Notre Dame 0 -- Jerome Schwartz scored on assists from Dwight 
Angelini and Scott Malin to give the Saracens (1-0-1) a nonleague victory at 
home. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 6, Canyon 0 -- Jill Gallegos scored two goals in the first day of pool 
play in the Simi Valley tournament. Agoura (3-0) received a forfeit win from 
Crescenta Valley earlier in the day. 
</P>
<P>
South Torrance tournament: Strikers Jen Evans and Amanda Love each scored two 
goals to lead Royal (2-0) to shutout victories over Miraleste and Redondo at 
South Torrance High. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Crespi 84, San Luis Obispo 78 -- Rasaan Hall had 28 points, 16 rebounds and 
three steals and John Curtin added 20 points to lead Crespi (2-1) over San Luis 
Obispo (1-2) in the third-place game of the San Luis Obispo tournament. 
</P>
<P>
La Canada 63, Camarillo 54 -- Richard Mandeville scored 20 points and 
tournament most valuable player Jeff Lord added 12 as the Spartans held off the 
Scorpions to win the Saugus Shootout at Saugus High. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus 77, San Fernando 55 -- Greg Yumbar had 27 points and 11 rebounds for 
Saugus in the consolation final of the Saugus Shootout. Teammate Jason Riggio 
had seven steals and six assists. Garrick Simpson scored 17 for San Fernando. 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 41, Antelope Valley 33 -- Jason Grimes scored 10 points to lead 
Palmdale (1-2) and Raynell Dunbar paced Antelope Valley (0-3) with 12 in the 
seventh-place game of the Saugus Shootout. TIM PERERA 
</P>
