<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
ST. PAUL KNOCKS OFF HAWTHORNE, 13-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID RAATZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Paul High fullback Anthony Morales scored two touchdowns and rushed for 53 
yards in seven carries to lead the Swordsmen to a 13-0 win over Hawthorne in a 
Southern Section Division III semifinal football playoff game at Cerritos 
College. 
</P>
<P>
St. Paul (8-3-2) will play undefeated Anaheim Esperanza (13-0) for the title 
next Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The Swordsmen will take a nine-game winning streak into the championship. 
</P>
<P>
St. Paul held Hawthorne (10-3) to two first downs (both on penalties) and three 
yards total offense in the first half en route to a 14-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Morrell Ollis, Hawthorne's 1,000-yard rusher, netted minus five yards on three 
first-half carries and finished with four yards on six carries. 
</P>
<P>
After a scoreless first quarter, Morales scored on a one-yard run on the 
initial play of the second quarter to give St. Paul a 7-0 lead. Morales' 
touchdown culminated a 13-play, 59-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
On the Swordsmen's next possession, tailback Carlos Ramos had a three-yard 
touchdown run, which finished off a 12-play, 62-yard drive. For the game, Ramos 
had 98 rushing yards on 19 attempts. 
</P>
<P>
St. Paul quarterback Albert Borunda threw for 111 yards (without an 
interception) on eight-of-13 passing. 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne quarterback Jamil Williams completed only five of 14 passes for 103 
yards. He had two passes intercepted. DAVID RAATZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
