<TEXT>
<P>
A former "China Beach" fan wrote to say (TV Times, Nov. 11) that she is unhappy 
with the changes that have taken place on the series this season. It would have 
been more comfortable to have stayed in China Beach with the characters we have 
come to know and cherish, and to further explore their relationships with one 
another. 
</P>
<P>
The show's constant change in time and place is often disorienting and 
confusing, but imagine what it is like for Vietnam veterans who still 
experience the flashbacks. These scenes allow the viewer to understand the 
emotions that trigger seemingly bizarre behavior. 
</P>
<P>
"China Beach" is never easy to watch. It's heart breaking and gut wrenching. It 
makes you laugh a little and cry a lot, but most important it makes you think 
and care. 
</P>
<P>
Patsy St. John, San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
