<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLUNTEER OPTIONS AS VARIED AS THE NEEDS; 
</P>
<P>
GENERAL INTEREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Cancer Society Discovery Shop: Sherman Oaks store needs volunteers to 
sort, price and help customers. Flexible hours, no experience necessary. 
Information: (818) 905-9141. 
</P>
<P>
AIDS Project Los Angeles: Through the holidays will be offering a volunteer 
training course for its hot line, 9 a.m. to noon Tuesdays and Thursdays, at 
6721 Romaine St., Los Angeles. Information: (213) 962-1600, Ext. 109. 
</P>
<P>
Alisa Ann Ruch California Burn Center: Canoga Park office needs volunteers to 
type and help with bulk mailings and addressing envelopes. Information (818) 
883-7700. 
</P>
<P>
American Red Cross: At 14717 Sherman Way, Van Nuys, needs CPR instructors, 
clerical assistants and bilingual assistants for the disaster hot line. 
Information: (818) 376-1700. 
</P>
<P>
Burbank Temporary Aid Center: Needs volunteers to help with holiday needs: 
making food baskets, working food lines and sorting donated items. Information: 
(818) 846-2330. 
</P>
<P>
Friends of the Family's Young Moms: Volunteer program needs women who became 
mothers at a young age to lead support groups. Extensive training is provided. 
Information (818) 988-4430. 
</P>
<P>
Focus Center: This Panorama City center needs volunteers for its drug-abuse and 
child-abuse prevention programs. Training is provided. Information: (818) 
989-4175. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Children Services 
</P>
<P>
Children's Home Society of California: Needs foster parents for children ages 5 
to 12. Information: (818) 908-5055. 
</P>
